Thailand Stocks: Precious Shipping, Siam Industrial, Sri Trang

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-09-21T09:44:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/bangchak-siam-industrial-credit-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index rose for a second day, gaining 3.31 points,
or 0.3 percent, to 1,029.59.  Rubber producers:  Sri Trang Agro-Industry Pcl (STA)  ,
Thailand’s biggest publicly traded rubber producer, dropped 5.6
percent to 20.20 baht, the lowest close since Sept. 14, 2010.
Thai Rubber Latex Corp. (Thailand) Pcl (TRUBB TB) declined 1.7
percent to 3.58 baht.  The cash price of Thai rubber fell 0.7 percent to 141.15
baht ($4.64) a kilogram today amid worries over global economic
slowdown, the Rubber Research Institute of Thailand said on its
website.  Precious Shipping Pcl (PSL)  , Thailand’s biggest shipping
company by market value, climbed 1.1 percent to 17.90 baht. The
Baltic Dry Index, a measure of shipping costs for commodities,
climbed 1.8 percent to 1,795 yesterday, the first advance in
four days, according to the  Baltic Exchange  in  London .  Siam Industrial Credit Pcl (SICCO)  , a  finance company ,
lost 2.7 percent to 5.35 baht, the lowest close since May 18.
Investors will have until the end of tomorrow to sell Siam
Industrial’s shares in a tender offer, the company said in a
regulatory filing. Siam Commercial Bank Pcl, Siam Industrial’s
biggest shareholder, has offered to buy the company’s shares it
doesn’t already own at 6.89 baht a share. The stock completed a
four-day, 22 percent slump.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  